Package de.fraunhofer.iais.eis

Interface RouteStep

  • All Superinterfaces:
    AppRoute, ModelClass
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    RouteStepImpl
    public interface RouteStep
extends ModelClass, AppRoute
    RouteSteps hold information about a communication pipelines between apps. A RouteStep should hold one value for the ids:appRouteStart and/or ids:appRouteEnd properties, so that communication between app endpoints remain distinguishable.

      • getRequiredDataApp

        AppRepresentation getRequiredDataApp()
        Refers to the concrete app representation (ids:AppRepresentation) for a data app (ids:DataApp) which is deployed in the Connector maintained by the Configuration Model and whoose endpoint (ids:AppEndpoint) is used in this ids:RouteStep. The referred app representation should be part of the catalog of AppResources in the corresponding Configuration Model (cf. ids:configuredAppResource property in class ids:ConfigurationModel). More information under https://w3id.org/idsa/core/requiredDataApp
        Returns:
        Returns the AppRepresentation for the property _requiredDataApp.

      • setRequiredDataApp

        void setRequiredDataApp​(AppRepresentation _requiredDataApp_)
        Refers to the concrete app representation (ids:AppRepresentation) for a data app (ids:DataApp) which is deployed in the Connector maintained by the Configuration Model and whoose endpoint (ids:AppEndpoint) is used in this ids:RouteStep. The referred app representation should be part of the catalog of AppResources in the corresponding Configuration Model (cf. ids:configuredAppResource property in class ids:ConfigurationModel). More information under https://w3id.org/idsa/core/requiredDataApp
